# Predictive Logistics Orchestrator MVP — Implementation Plan

## Project Overview
Build a hackathon MVP: an AI-driven logistics dashboard that predicts delivery delays in real-time using traffic, weather, and warehouse metrics. Stack: Firebase Firestore, Python ML (scikit-learn), Leaflet.js, vanilla JS.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Firebase credentials:** The project uses `firebase-admin` (Python) and the Firebase JS SDK (frontend). You must supply:
> 1. A **service account key** (`credentials.json`) in the project root for the Python backend/worker/simulator.
> 2. Your **Firebase web app config** (apiKey, authDomain, projectId, etc.) — I will place a placeholder in the frontend `app.js` that you need to fill in.
>
> Without these, the app will scaffold correctly but won't connect to Firebase.

> [!NOTE]
> The ML pipeline generates **synthetic** training data and trains a local model (`model.pkl`). No real dataset is required. The model is intentionally simple (Random Forest) for fast inference.

