### Shared Configuration

#### [NEW] [firebase_config.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/firebase_config.py)
Initializes `firebase_admin` from `credentials.json` and exports a shared `db` (Firestore client). All Python modules import from here.

---

### ML Pipeline

#### [NEW] [ml_pipeline/generate_mock_data.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/ml_pipeline/generate_mock_data.py)
- Generates **1,000 rows** of synthetic logistics data as CSV.
- Features: `current_speed_kmh`, `weather_condition`, `traffic_index`, `warehouse_backlog_index`, `distance_remaining`.
- Targets: `is_delayed` (bool), `delay_minutes` (int).
- Correlation logic: high traffic + bad weather + high backlog → high delay probability.
- Output: `ml_pipeline/training_data.csv`.

#### [NEW] [ml_pipeline/train_model.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/ml_pipeline/train_model.py)
- Reads CSV, one-hot-encodes `weather_condition`.
- Trains a `RandomForestClassifier` (delay probability) and `RandomForestRegressor` (delay minutes).
- Saves both as a single dict in `ml_pipeline/model.pkl` using joblib.
- Prints accuracy/MAE metrics on a test split.

---

### Backend

#### [NEW] [backend/seed_firestore.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/backend/seed_firestore.py)
- Populates Firestore `shipments` collection with 5 demo shipments (New Delhi region routes).
- Populates `live_tracking` collection with initial positions matching each shipment.

#### [NEW] [backend/ml_worker.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/backend/ml_worker.py)
- Loads `model.pkl`.
- Uses `on_snapshot()` to listen to the `live_tracking` collection.
- On every change: extracts features, calculates `distance_remaining` (haversine), runs inference, writes `ml_delay_probability` and `ml_estimated_delay_mins` back to the document.

#### [NEW] [backend/api.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/backend/api.py)
- FastAPI app with `POST /api/trigger_storm/{shipment_id}`.
- Sets `weather_condition = 'Storm'` and `traffic_index = 10` in Firestore for the given shipment.
- Allows judges to trigger a dramatic demo scenario.

---

### Simulation

#### [NEW] [simulation/simulator.py](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/simulation/simulator.py)
- `while True` loop with `time.sleep(3)`.
- Moves each active shipment's `current_lat`/`current_lng` toward destination.
- Randomly fluctuates `current_speed_kmh`, `traffic_index`, and occasionally `weather_condition`.
- Updates `live_tracking` documents via `doc_ref.update()`.

---

### Frontend Dashboard

#### [NEW] [frontend/index.html](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/frontend/index.html)
- Single-page app: loads Leaflet.js (CDN), Firebase JS SDK (CDN), `style.css`, `app.js`.
- Contains map container, control panel with "Simulate Severe Storm" button, and a shipment info sidebar.

#### [NEW] [frontend/style.css](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/frontend/style.css)
- Premium dark theme with glassmorphism control panel.
- Smooth animations for marker status changes and panel interactions.
- Responsive layout; full-screen map with floating overlays.

#### [NEW] [frontend/app.js](file:///c:/Users/ASUS/Predictive%20Logistics%20and%20Societal%20Impact/frontend/app.js)
- Initializes Firebase with placeholder config (user fills in).
- Creates Leaflet map centered on New Delhi.
- `onSnapshot()` listener on `live_tracking` — creates/updates color-coded markers (green/yellow/red based on delay probability thresholds).
- Marker click → tooltip with Shipment ID, ETA delay, explainability factors.
- "Simulate Storm" button calls the FastAPI endpoint.

